New note

To get started enter a title for your note above. Once your text cursor leaves
the first line the name of the buffer will be set to match your note’s title.
You can then save this note using Vim’s built in :write and :update commands.

                                    * * *

The notes plug-in comes with self hosting documentation. To jump to these notes
position your text on the highlighted name and press ‘gf’ in normal mode:

 • Note taking syntax
 • Note taking commands
